Even though the NBA has an average annual salary of nearly $7 million, about one-third of the league’s players are probably “hurting” for money right now, C.J.
McCollum, of the Portland Trailblazers, was speaking with NBA analyst Jay Williams, who asked how many players the All-Star guard thought might be living paycheck-to-paycheck.
“There’s some guys in the league that are hurting right now because … there could be a pay stoppage,” McCollum said in part.
Among them is Brooklyn Nets star Kevin Durant, who announced last month that he had tested positive for the coronavirus.
The NBA Draft could be pushed back months into September, Wojnarowski reported Sunday.